WEBVTT

00:38.210 --> 00:40.419
[train clanking]

00:50.843 --> 00:53.570
[train rumbling on tracks]

01:05.341 --> 01:07.929
[lock clicks]

01:07.964 --> 01:10.518
[bell jingles]

01:12.693 --> 01:14.315
To the naked eye,

01:14.350 --> 01:16.973
a suit appears to consist
of two parts:

01:17.007 --> 01:19.631
a jacket and trousers.

01:23.324 --> 01:26.569
But those two
seemingly solid parts

01:26.603 --> 01:29.503
are composed of
four different fabrics.

01:31.815 --> 01:35.716
Cotton, silk, mohair and wool.

01:37.511 --> 01:42.343
And those four fabrics are
cut into 38 separate pieces.

01:43.689 --> 01:48.004
The process of sizing, forming,
conjoining those pieces

01:48.038 --> 01:52.802
requires no fewer than
228 steps.

02:00.844 --> 02:03.088
[teakettle whistling]

02:27.423 --> 02:30.564
So the first step
is measurement.

02:49.272 --> 02:54.415
But "measurement" doesn'’t mean,
uh, just reaching for your tape,

02:54.450 --> 02:57.073
"So many inches here,
so many inches there."

02:57.107 --> 02:58.868
No, no, no.

03:26.413 --> 03:29.105
You cannot make something good

03:30.900 --> 03:34.800
